## Unified Measurement Platforms

These tools go beyond MTA to include MMM and incrementality—the triangulation approach.

### mbuzz

**Best for:** Teams wanting validated, server-side attribution without enterprise pricing

| Aspect | Details |
|--------|---------|
| **Pricing** | Free (50K events), $29/mo (1M), $99/mo (5M), $299/mo (25M) |
| **Setup Time** | 10 minutes |
| **Tracking** | Server-side (95%+ event capture) |
| **Unique Feature** | 8 attribution models + custom DSL + incrementality testing |

**Strengths:**
- Server-side tracking bypasses ad blockers—captures 95%+ of events vs 70% with client-side
- 8 built-in models: First Touch, Last Touch, Linear, Time Decay, U-Shaped, W-Shaped, Markov Chain, Shapley Value
- Custom attribution models via simple DSL—define your own logic in minutes
- Side-by-side model comparison shows how credit shifts between channels
- LTV attribution tracks recurring revenue back to original acquisition
- Incrementality testing validates whether attribution is actually accurate
- Native SDKs for Rails, Django, Laravel, Node.js—no tag manager required
- Transparent pricing, no sales calls, export everything anytime

**Limitations:**
- Newer player with less market presence than established tools
- No built-in podcast/TV proxy tracking (digital-focused)
- Requires server-side integration (not drop-in pixel)

**Best fit:** Technical teams who want validated attribution without black-box models or enterprise pricing. Especially strong for SaaS, e-commerce, and any business wanting to prove—not just model—channel impact.

